I am Professor of Information Management at the Berlin School of Library and Information Science at Humboldt-Universität zu Berlin, and Scientific Consultant for Open Science at the Helmholtz Association’s Open Science Office.


On this website, you will find information about my work and research.


Blogging


While not always as frequently as I’d like, I blog about innovations in scholarly communication at  wisspub.net.


At Humboldt-Universität zu Berlin, our Research Group Information Management hosts a virtual research lab, where we regularly share updates on our projects and research:  infomgnt.org


Contact


The best way to reach me is by email: heinz.pampel@hu-berlin.de


Profiles on the Web


ORCID:  https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3334-2771


My social media profiles:  Mastodon,  Bluesky,  LinkedIn,  Twitter (in order of usage).


